<p>Our work in outcomes and assessment is a significant part of a four-step process designed to help us improve learning and teaching at BYU-Idaho. &nbsp;Those four steps are:</p>
<p><strong style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;"><img height="253" src="Images/instructional-development/Outcomes%20and%20Assessment/Improvement%20spiral.png" /></strong></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">1. &nbsp;Articulate/revise learning outcomes.</span></p>
<div>
<div style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">2. &nbsp;Design assessments/Work with the evidence.</span><br /><br />3. &nbsp;Plan learning experiences/Take informed action.<br /><br />4. &nbsp;Reflect and revise for continuous improvement.<br /><br />There are links in the menu on the left for each of the four steps. &nbsp;Please explore the information presented in those pages, discuss them with your colleagues, and be sure to take a look at the recommended readings available <a href="http://www.byui.edu/outcomes-and-assessment" target="_blank">here</a>.</div>
